<Link id="l00074" /><CodeLine lineNumber="74"><span class="doxyHighlight">&#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00075" /><CodeLine lineNumber="75"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00076" /><CodeLine lineNumber="76"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The order in the returned sequence is the order of reaching defs in the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00077" /><CodeLine lineNumber="77"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// upward traversal: the first def is the closest to the given reference RefA,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00078" /><CodeLine lineNumber="78"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// the next one is further up, and so on.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00079" /><CodeLine lineNumber="79"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The list ends at a reaching phi def, or when the reference from RefA is</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00080" /><CodeLine lineNumber="80"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// covered by the defs in the list (see FullChain).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00081" /><CodeLine lineNumber="81"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// This function provides two modes of operation:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00082" /><CodeLine lineNumber="82"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// (1) Returning the sequence of reaching defs for a particular reference</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00083" /><CodeLine lineNumber="83"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// node. This sequence will terminate at the first phi node &#91;1&#93;.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00084" /><CodeLine lineNumber="84"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// (2) Returning a partial sequence of reaching defs, where the final goal</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00085" /><CodeLine lineNumber="85"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// is to traverse past phi nodes to the actual defs arising from the code</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00086" /><CodeLine lineNumber="86"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// itself.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00087" /><CodeLine lineNumber="87"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// In mode (2), the register reference for which the search was started</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00088" /><CodeLine lineNumber="88"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// may be different from the reference node RefA, for which this call was</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00089" /><CodeLine lineNumber="89"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// made, hence the argument RefRR, which holds the original register.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00090" /><CodeLine lineNumber="90"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Also, some definitions may have already been encountered in a previous</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00091" /><CodeLine lineNumber="91"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// call that will influence register covering. The register references</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00092" /><CodeLine lineNumber="92"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// already defined are passed in through DefRRs.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00093" /><CodeLine lineNumber="93"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// In mode (1), the &quot;continuation&quot; considerations do not apply, and the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00094" /><CodeLine lineNumber="94"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// RefRR is the same as the register in RefA, and the set DefRRs is empty.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00095" /><CodeLine lineNumber="95"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00096" /><CodeLine lineNumber="96"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// &#91;1&#93; It is possible for multiple phi nodes to be included in the returned</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00098" /><CodeLine lineNumber="98"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   SubA = phi ...</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00099" /><CodeLine lineNumber="99"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   SubB = phi ...</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00100" /><CodeLine lineNumber="100"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   ...  = SuperAB(rdef:SubA), SuperAB&quot;(rdef:SubB)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00101" /><CodeLine lineNumber="101"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// However, these phi nodes are independent from one another in terms of</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00102" /><CodeLine lineNumber="102"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// the data-flow.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00103" /><CodeLine lineNumber="103"></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00253" /><CodeLine lineNumber="253"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//                     covered if we added A first, and A would be covered</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00630" /><CodeLine lineNumber="630"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00631" /><CodeLine lineNumber="631"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Propagate the reached registers up in the phi chain.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00632" /><CodeLine lineNumber="632"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00633" /><CodeLine lineNumber="633"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The following type of situation needs careful handling:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00634" /><CodeLine lineNumber="634"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00635" /><CodeLine lineNumber="635"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   phi d1&lt;R1:0&gt;  (1)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00636" /><CodeLine lineNumber="636"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//        |</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00637" /><CodeLine lineNumber="637"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   ... d2&lt;R1&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00638" /><CodeLine lineNumber="638"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//        |</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00639" /><CodeLine lineNumber="639"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   phi u3&lt;R1:0&gt;  (2)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00640" /><CodeLine lineNumber="640"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//        |</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00641" /><CodeLine lineNumber="641"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   ... u4&lt;R1&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00642" /><CodeLine lineNumber="642"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00643" /><CodeLine lineNumber="643"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The phi node (2) defines a register pair R1:0, and reaches a &quot;real&quot;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00644" /><CodeLine lineNumber="644"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// use u4 of just R1. The same phi node is also known to reach (upwards)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00645" /><CodeLine lineNumber="645"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// the phi node (1). However, the use u4 is not reached by phi (1),</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00646" /><CodeLine lineNumber="646"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// because of the intervening definition d2 of R1. The data flow between</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00647" /><CodeLine lineNumber="647"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// phis (1) and (2) is restricted to R1:0 minus R1, i.e. R0.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00648" /><CodeLine lineNumber="648"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00649" /><CodeLine lineNumber="649"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// When propagating uses up the phi chains, get the all reaching defs</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00650" /><CodeLine lineNumber="650"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// for a given phi use, and traverse the list until the propagated ref</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00651" /><CodeLine lineNumber="651"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// is covered, or until reaching the final phi. Only assume that the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00652" /><CodeLine lineNumber="652"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// reference reaches the phi in the latter case.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00653" /><CodeLine lineNumber="653"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00654" /><CodeLine lineNumber="654"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The operation &quot;clearIn&quot; can be expensive. For a given set of intervening</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00655" /><CodeLine lineNumber="655"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// defs, cache the result of subtracting these defs from a given register</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00656" /><CodeLine lineNumber="656"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// ref.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00657" /><CodeLine lineNumber="657"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">using </span><span class="doxyHighlight">RefHash = std::hash&lt;RegisterRef&gt;;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00660" /><CodeLine lineNumber="660"><span class="doxyHighlight">  std::unordered&#95;map&lt;RegisterAggr, SubMap&gt; Subs;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00661" /><CodeLine lineNumber="661"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">auto</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> ClearIn = &#91;&#93;(<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/rdf/registerref">RegisterRef</a> RR, </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/rdf/registeraggr">RegisterAggr</a> &amp;Mid, SubMap &amp;SM) &#123;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00672" /><CodeLine lineNumber="672"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Go over all phis.</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00683" /><CodeLine lineNumber="683"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/rdf/registeraggr">RegisterAggr</a> &amp;MidDefs = <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/option/option-cpp/#a04665169063c8ca1f2ea96c27fc7c2b2">P</a>.second;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00684" /><CodeLine lineNumber="684"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Collect the set PropUp of uses that are reached by the current</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00685" /><CodeLine lineNumber="685"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// phi PA, and are not covered by any intervening def between the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00686" /><CodeLine lineNumber="686"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// currently visited use UA and the upward phi P.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00687" /><CodeLine lineNumber="687"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00688" /><CodeLine lineNumber="688"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (MidDefs.<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/rdf/registeraggr/#abe99acebac6f58f70d09de84f5becbdf">hasCoverOf</a>(UR))</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00689" /><CodeLine lineNumber="689"><span class="doxyHighlight">          </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">continue</span><span class="doxyHighlight">;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00690" /><CodeLine lineNumber="690"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (Subs.find(MidDefs) == Subs.end()) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00691" /><CodeLine lineNumber="691"><span class="doxyHighlight">          Subs.insert(&#123;MidDefs, SubMap(1, RefHash(), RefEqual(PRI))&#125;);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00692" /><CodeLine lineNumber="692"><span class="doxyHighlight">        &#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00693" /><CodeLine lineNumber="693"><span class="doxyHighlight">        SubMap &amp;SM = Subs.at(MidDefs);</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00695" /><CodeLine lineNumber="695"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// General algorithm:</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00985" /><CodeLine lineNumber="985"><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">void</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> Liveness::traverse(<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/machinebasicblock">MachineBasicBlock</a> &#42;<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/ir/builtingcs-cpp/#ae76959fe811ba090de4cba69ac00f1da">B</a>, RefMap &amp;LiveIn) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00986" /><CodeLine lineNumber="986"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The LiveIn map, for each (physical) register, contains the set of live</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00987" /><CodeLine lineNumber="987"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// reaching defs of that register that are live on entry to the associated</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00988" /><CodeLine lineNumber="988"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// block.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00989" /><CodeLine lineNumber="989"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00990" /><CodeLine lineNumber="990"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The summary of the traversal algorithm:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00991" /><CodeLine lineNumber="991"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00992" /><CodeLine lineNumber="992"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// R is live-in in B, if there exists a U(R), such that rdef(R) dom B</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00993" /><CodeLine lineNumber="993"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// and (U \\in IDF(B) or B dom U).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00994" /><CodeLine lineNumber="994"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00995" /><CodeLine lineNumber="995"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// for (C : children) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00996" /><CodeLine lineNumber="996"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   LU = &#123;&#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00997" /><CodeLine lineNumber="997"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   traverse(C, LU)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00998" /><CodeLine lineNumber="998"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   LiveUses += LU</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00999" /><CodeLine lineNumber="999"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// &#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01000" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1000"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01001" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1001"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// LiveUses -= Defs(B);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01002" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1002"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// LiveUses += UpwardExposedUses(B);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01003" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1003"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// for (C : IIDF&#91;B&#93;)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01004" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1004"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   for (U : LiveUses)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01005" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1005"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//     if (Rdef(U) dom C)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01006" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1006"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//       C.addLiveIn(U)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01007" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1007"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01008" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1008"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01009" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1009"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Go up the dominator tree (depth-first).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01010" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1010"><span class="doxyHighlight">  <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a94b65b831ad8756f7d3a029a1e599f75">MachineDomTreeNode</a> &#42;<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/support/regcomp-c/#a0240ac851181b84ac374872dc5434ee4">N</a> = MDT.<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/dominatortreebase/#ad8295b9b507d1d847cd46856f8255eab">getNode</a>(<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/ir/builtingcs-cpp/#ae76959fe811ba090de4cba69ac00f1da">B</a>);</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01012" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1012"><span class="doxyHighlight">    <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/rdf/liveness/#ae0aea4a799ad5f9d4015066269451fb1">RefMap</a> L;</span></CodeLine>
